 on, its true. What do you think those ageing Pokemon players are going to be playing as soon as the switch in their head that says kiddie shows are cool, flips to the action and sci-fi shows are cool side. Jeez, I'm starting to depress myself. In my humble opinion I think we should all turn our attention from writing protest letters to WotC, to instead writing letters to Decipher to start a new game based (though maybe not entirely) on the Star Wars mechanic. The Matrix and Final Fantasy have been mentioned. I'm sure Squaresoft and whoever owns the Matrix would be willing to cut a licensing deal. Heck with Final Fantasy you could also put out an RPG. That would give WotC competition for both its key products. Don't get me wrong, I don't dislike WotC. In fact I love AD&D and Star Wars RPG, but I also loved Star Wars CCG... partially because of the mechanic and I would like to at least see that live on. Those are my thoughts. </font></td></tr><tr><td><font face=arial size=2 color=#FFFFFF>xavier six</font><font face=arial size=2 color=#FFFFFF> - Wed Jan 9 2002  </font></td></tr></table><p><table width=100%><tr><td><HR><font face=arial size=2 color=#FFFFFF>If I read corrct between the lines it states that the desicion was made in an early stage, but they never mentioned. And i you read the stuff correct, it has $ signs all over the article...</font></td></tr><tr><td><font face=arial size=2 color=#FFFFFF>Mister Boba Fett</font><font face=arial size=2 color=#FFFFFF> - Wed Jan 9 2002  </font></td></tr></table><p><table width=100%><tr><td><HR><font face=arial size=2 color=#FFFFFF>Now there's the professional response to the break-up of a partnership.  I really don't get the outcry against Lucasfilms, they never made any promise to any of you.  They entered into a contract w/ Decipher, and at the end of that contract decided not to renew it as a business decision.  I don't really get what's to be so mad about, sure, you're mad that the game you play is now gonna die, but it