<br>
I.E. The existing game was too hard for stupid people.  Go figure.<br>
</font></td></tr><tr><td><font face=arial size=2 color=#FFFFFF><a href="mailto:FirebirdJCT@aol.com">Echo 1</a></font><font face=arial size=2 color=#FFFFFF> - Tue Jan 15 2002  </font></td></tr></table><p><table width=100%><tr><td><HR><font face=arial size=2 color=#FFFFFF>that ...was a pile.</font></td></tr><tr><td><font face=arial size=2 color=#FFFFFF>snider</font><font face=arial size=2 color=#FFFFFF> - Tue Jan 15 2002  </font></td></tr></table><p><table width=100%><tr><td><HR><font face=arial size=2 color=#FFFFFF>Yeah, ummm, I don't know if he knows it, but MtG is a TCG, and on top of that, any trained monkey could learn the game. It's just too easy. </font></td></tr><tr><td><font face=arial size=2 color=#FFFFFF>Megascrub</font><font face=arial size=2 color=#FFFFFF> - Tue Jan 15 2002  </font></td></tr></table><p><table width=100%><tr><td><HR><font face=arial size=2 color=#FFFFFF>Ummm, Besides Magic what SUCCESSFUL games has WotC created?  Pokemon doesn't count, as it is merely a translation of a game that already existed.  So tell me, what have they created that's so great?  Harry Potter?  Zena, Hercules?  Showdown?  They haven't been able to put out a quality game in 6 years, what makes you think this one won't suck too?<br>
<br>
</font></td></tr><tr><td><font face=arial size=2 color=#FFFFFF><a href="mailto:tony_heather@ameritech.net">Dark h2o</a></font><font face=arial size=2 color=#FFFFFF> - Tue Jan 15 2002  </font></td></tr></table><p><table width=100%><tr><td><HR><font face=arial size=2 color=#FFFFFF>This is a crap idea just to get money. I mean how many people are really gonna start the new game anyway. SWCCG is the best CCG at the momment. I believe even though you guys need your money, this was a stupid idea.</font></td></tr><tr><td><font face=arial size=2 color=#FFFFFF><a href="mailto:empire161@hotmail.com">wickid</a></font><font face=arial size=2 color=#FFFFFF> - Wed Jan 16 2002  </font></td></tr></table><p><table width=100%><tr><td><HR><font face=arial size=2 color=#FFFFFF>Hey there,<br><br>
<br><br>
I'd like to say something too, it's become quite a long story, so if you don't want to read it ... you better stop right here.<br><br>
<br><br>
Back in the days I started playing Magic right after legends. I loved it. That is until 4th Edition and Homelands came along. Then I quit. I also couldn't keep up anymore with all the expansions. <br><br>
<br><br>
Than I turned to SW:CCG and loved that even more.  I didn't really feel motivated to collect enitire sets of Magic, I did have that motivation with Star Wars (mainly because I like SW since I was a kid). So I was playing and collecting and I was able to do so financially, because only one or two expansions came out every year.<br><br>
<br><br>
Now that the game is coming to it's end I'm feeling sad, but I'm also hopeful.<br><br>
<br><br>
I'm sad to see a good game die. And be frank, how many of you will be playing this for years to come. I'll sure try, but without new expansions ... ? Many players will drop the game entirely and go look for something else. Hopefully it won't happen, though. I still hope Decipher or any other company is going to find a way to add new cards to the game without violating any copyrights.<br><br>
I'm also sad as a collector, because it would have been nice to have a collection of cards ranging from Episode 1 to Episode 6. I still don't think it was a waste of money. So what if your Vader isn't worth anything anymore this time next year. I never bought any cards to sell them again. I bought them for my collection. And my collection of cards remains long after april 2002.<br><br>
<br>  <br>
I'm hopefull though that the new card game will be very good as well. The dice thing may scare people of in the beginning, but you can't track the roll of the dice... We'll just have to see how it turns out. I just hope that WotC isn't going to eventually kill this game as they did Magic with to many expansions, banned and restricted lists and simplifying the game (because some people might not understand the meaning of the word "Tap"). <br><br>
<br><br>
I will probably buy a starter of the new game to check it out. I hope it has photos on the cards instead of drawn pictures, such as with Jedi Knights. Note: You won't hurt WotC by not buying their new Star Wars game. You may even deprive yourself of a great game ... who knows? I do hope that it will attract a lot of people, so there are a lot of people to play against. In my Magic days it wasn't hard to find a group of Magic players. But I do not know very many SW:CCG players in my city.<br><br>
<br><br>
Don't get me wrong here. I'm not trying to put SW:CCG down. I love the game and even now I'm still trying to come up with new deck ideas. Even if I'm going to play the new game, I'll be taking out my old SW:CCG decks once in a while just for fun. It's a great game and a great game doesn't die. People will still play the game, maybe just not at the level it is played these days. Let's just hope the new game is worth it. I hope it's a successor worthy of the name Star Wars followed by the letters C(ard)G(ame).<br><br>
<br><br>
See ya,<br>
Dschadir (Jeroen)</font></td></tr><tr><td><font face=arial size=2 color=#FFFFFF><a href="mailto:j.sintanneland@wxs.nl">Dschadir</a></font><font face=arial size=2 color=#FFFFFF> - Wed Jan 16 2002  </font></td></tr></table><p><table width=100%><tr><td><HR><font face=arial size=2 color=#FFFFFF>thanks to all that played the game. Its not dead just retired after a great great run. Now we keep it alive in our hearts and we keep playing like we always did. Dont let WotC get you down they suck anyways. SO i say to all you players of this game thank you thank you thank you for always being the best players in ccg. We woul dplay magic its just that we would to easy so whats the fun it that. Thank you guys <br>
ben wilson Louisville swccg tournament director amd always will be</font></td></tr><tr><td><font face=arial size=2 color=#FFFFFF><a href="mailto:losville502@aol.com">anteup</a></font><font face=arial size=2 color=#FFFFFF> - Thu Jan 17 2002  </font></td></tr></table><p><table width=100%><tr><td><HR><font face=arial size=2 color=#FFFFFF>Unfortunately but you have to blame it on Lucas. He's shareholder of Hasbro, Hasbro owns WotC, WotC just had to get SWCCG. <br>
<br>
I've played Magic, but after Exodus it just become too crappy, with coountless clarifications of even basic rules. Not to mention worst move ever in any game - to ban something. Other fact that irritated lot of the best M:TG players in may region (Croatia) was constant change of the play environment for the tournaments.<br>
<br>
Then SW:CCG came. I immediately switched (was in fact with a friend first player there), and in last 6 years seen slow but steady grow of player community. For a time I even played few different CCGs - M:TG, Jyhad - V:TES, Spellfire, Alien vs. Predator, X-files just to name few. But lost interest in all of them (except Spellfire - it's just plain fun and sometimes hillarious) because of unique approach that Decipher offered with SW:CCG. It was freom the start more versatile, and metagaming was harder than for the M:TG. you still needed to invest a lot, but you just didn't needed most expensive cards to be able to play competitively.<br>
<br>
We won't change anything regarding new WotC SWCCG, but at the same time my oppinion is that it will downgrade whole SW community. Despite all his influence and previous results Richard Garfield isn't world's greates game designer - what the heck - he isn't even good one. WotC destroyed some of the finest licences in gaming like Battletech and Dune. They even failed to cash in temporary popularity of the licences of  Hercules and Xena. They sold V:TES to White Wolf, and suddenly it started flourishing, and what I heard is that L5R is out of the WotC umbrella. I just hope it will progress. <br>
<br>
Decipher made a lots of mistakes, but it cannot be compared to just plain stupidity that WotC tried to force upon players with semi finished products over last 10 years. </font></td></tr><tr><td><font face=arial size=2 color=#FFFFFF><a href="mailto:kradanov@rocketmail.com">Grand Moff Maleus</a></font><font face=arial size=2 color=#FFFFFF> - Fri Jan 18 2002  </font></td></tr></table><p><table width=100%><tr><td><HR><font face=arial size=2 color=#FFFFFF>HAH his post is a whole load of BS! I wish i could express my self better. With more aprorprate word.....#^&@!&$&*^#&^%*&#@%^#&%#&#%*#@</font></td></tr><tr><td><font face=arial size=2 color=#FFFFFF>MAn your a  chump</font><font face=arial size=2 color=#FFFFFF> - Mon Jan 21 2002  </font></td></tr></table><p><table width=100%><tr><td><HR><font face=arial size=2 color=#FFFFFF>Wizards of the Coast IS an enemy if you play something they don't own.  They are on a path to be the only company in the industry.  They want to destroy/own every property and company in existence.  Good for business?  Sure!  Good for gamers?  Not by a long shot!<br><br>
Man, I miss ICE.  I'm shocked Wotc didn't throw all the money they had at Lord of the Rings to boot.  Give them time...I'm sure they didn't expect the movie to be as great and successful as it is.  If this happens, you will once again consider them the enemy as they bid for the rights to the game...and create a new one, where Gandalf gets to roll four dice against the Balrog, only to have the Balrog "Evade" by spending resources/ flipping a coin/ using Bulbasaur blast power or whatever.<br><br>
I used to really root for that little company no one had heard of, WotC.  I wish that were still the way things were.</font></td></tr><tr><td><font face=arial size=2 color=#FFFFFF>Richard Garfield Sux</font><font face=arial size=2 color=#FFFFFF> - Mon Jan 21 2002  </font></td></tr></table><p><table width=100%><tr><td><HR><font face=arial size=2 color=#FFFFFF>If simplifying SWCCG ( which is exactly what WotC is going to do) will improve this game, then i'm a flaming monkey.</font></td></tr><tr><td><font face=arial size=2 color=#FFFFFF>The Star Wars Fan</font><font face=arial size=2 color=#FFFFFF> - Thu Jan 24 2002  </font></td></tr></table><p><table width=100%><tr><td><HR><font face=arial size=2 color=#FFFFFF>can anyone say Micro$oft?</font></td></tr><tr><td><font face=arial size=2 color=#FFFFFF>suck</font><font face=arial size=2 color=#FFFFFF> - Thu Jan 24 2002  </font></td></tr></table><p><table width=100%><tr><td><HR><font face=arial size=2 color=#FFFFFF>Ladies & Gentlemen.<br>
<br>
  Just because WotC took the license from Decipher doesnt mean the game is going to die. Once LucasArts sees that WotC mess up with Star Wars, they are gonna be hard pressed to find another company to make the cards. With WotC gone, Decipher will be the most worthy cantidate. Star Wars will survive, even if no new expansions come off the press anytime soom, so what? You know the inevetable, Decipher will get the licence back, and we just have to bide our time till they do. Besides, this will give the newer players a chance to catch up with the more experienced players, collection wise. This card game wont die intil we abandon it. That is why im proposing a Pro Tour for SWCCG for all players in the state of New Jersey. Join my group, MrQuestor's SWCCG NJ Pro Tourney. Anyone from NJ (or surrounding areas) are welcome, new players and experienced players alike. If i can find a sponsor, i think i can scrounge up some prize support and trophies for winners. This tour will be a continuing, 5-7 week tour, where, at the end, the players with the highest combined score will win cards of their choice (most likely, no guarantees yet) and trophies(if i can get a sponsor). There is only one problem. Im 14, and Im not sure if anyone wants to play with a 14 year old Tournament Director. If ya wanna join, join my group, and start having fun. If you dont wanna join and your in my area, remember, its not just your loss, its also Deciphers and SWCCGs loss.<br>
<br>
"A God Among Gods"</font></td></tr><tr><td><font face=arial size=2 color=#FFFFFF><a href="mailto:renegadequestor@hotmail.com">MrQuestor</a></font><font face=arial size=2 color=#FFFFFF> - Sat Jan 26 2002  </font></td></tr></table><p><table width=100%><tr><td><HR><font face=arial size=2 color=#FFFFFF>It's been a long time for me. I got into the SWCCG back in January of 1996. I played off and on in tournaments from the beginning of 1996 to the spring of 2000. I stopped playing in tournaments because they're weren't fun anymore. Once in a while, I could play a decent match. Most of the time, I got beaten down like a schoolgirl. But I kept on collecting. At last count, I had well over 20,000 cards sitting in storage. The problem wasn't with tournaments.<br>
<br>
The problem was that I couldn't find anyone who wanted to play after 1998. The game grew too complicated and expensive for most casual gamers to jump into. One look at the novel that is the rules glossary and people would back away from it. I like the game and I always have. However, I think its time is up. <br>
<br>
It was a good run and I had a great time playing and collecting. However, I can't play it anymore because I can't find anyone who wants to try it. Let the new game emerge. Give it a chance before declaring it the spawn of all that is unholy. <br>
<br>
I didn't pick the game up in the first place because it was made by Decipher. I picked it up because it was Star Wars. When the new game comes out, I won't give much thought about who makes it as I will about how it plays. </font></td></tr><tr><td><font face=arial size=2 color=#FFFFFF>Psion</font><font face=arial size=2 color=#FFFFFF> - Sat Jan 26 2002  </font></td></tr></table><p><table width=100%><tr><td><HR><font face=arial size=2 color=#FFFFFF>I was thinking of putting a black band on my arm to mourn the recent events. But after reading all of your comments, I have had time to think a little bit. And instead I feel very happy! I am actually quite happy that the game is OVER. There will be no more expansions and I think it is GREAT! Now I can focus on getting my collection complete and also I KNOW what cards will be there - these cards will last FOREVER and live ETERNALLY! Great! I know there are plenty of people who has a really big collections out there, and sure, some people may want to throw them all away - for me that is fine as well because that will only make the surviving cards rarer and more worth. And just think of it, I have like 10 albums full of cards in my bookshelf and I LOVE just looking at them, I love reading the info on them. The value will never diminish. I think I have won in either way.<br>
<br>
Also, I really hated the Episode I cards and I would never have bought Theed Palace, for instance. I was tired of getting all those foil cards in the reflections sets as well, but I think it was a cool idea nevertheless. Especially I liked getting to see the personifications of Mara Jade, Guri, Dash Rendar, Talon Karrde, Thrawn, Mirax Terrik (WHAT A BABE!) - for me these are the only persons who will ever be these personas 'in the flesh'. I just wish I knew their names!<br>
<br>
So, don't think this was bad. Think of it like the bird Phoenix. It will arise! I for one will not use much time, energy and money on anything else when I have invested so much into this game. I will continue to do so. And so will others.<br>
<br>
'..we shall overcome..' <img src=/news/smileys/smile.gif><br>
<br>
</font></td></tr><tr><td><font face=arial size=2 color=#FFFFFF><a href="mailto:sindreaa@stud.ntnu.no">Sindre</a></font><font face=arial size=2 color=#FFFFFF> - Mon Jan 28 2002  </font></td></tr></table><p><table width=100%><tr><td><HR><font face=arial size=2 color=#FFFFFF>Would you rather not have a game at all? <br>
<br>
I am happy that WotC owns it now because SWCCG is a dying breed, there are no players in my area and that is solely based on the fact that it is so increadably difficult to learn.  On top of that, there is no fun for experianced players playing newbies, its like hitting the bowl there is no difficulty.  Now a new company owns the game, the players that thought it was too complicated will have a chance to enjoy themselves, and it is time for a fresh start.  <br>
<br>
I play the game for love of the universe, thats all, game mechanics, licencing, and who makes who is unimportant, as long as I have fun doing what I love.</font></td></tr><tr><td><font face=arial size=2 color=#FFFFFF>Jason</font><font face=arial size=2 color=#FFFFFF> - Tue Jan 29 2002  </font></td></tr></table><p><table width=100%><tr><td><HR><font face=arial size=2 color=#FFFFFF>i agree its kinda nice to be starting over, just the wotc game, or any other, probably won't be half as good as swccg. but your right, swccg's days were numbered already thanks to decipher bungeling.</font></td></tr><tr><td><font face=arial size=2 color=#FFFFFF>edmund</font><font face=arial size=2 color=#FFFFFF> - Tue Jan 29 2002  </font></td></tr></table><p><table width=100%><tr><td><HR><font face=arial size=2 color=#FFFFFF>Seriously, post a reply if you would play a Matrix CCG based on the SW Mechanic.. Just sort out a few of the location bugs and you have the most compatible system for a Matrix style game. No doubt about the SW Mechanic being the all time greatest, but imagine combining it with the Matrix! added bonus for D is that there are sequals coming out and an expanded universe in the comics. <br><br>
If you have intrest please reply to this post and write to Decipher to convince them. I already have at least 10 times over the past year alone...<br><br>
The only problem i can see is that Warner Brothers have told all companys that have access to the B5 license to Cease and desist production of there games (Precedence as an example, and the rights to the DVD release).<br>
<br><br>
Come on People, a great new game using the old system, how could you say no. Email, phone call, snail mail, carrier pigeon even, just get the message to D!!!!</font></td></tr><tr><td><font face=arial size=2 color=#FFFFFF>Wizard</font><font face=arial size=2 color=#FFFFFF> - Tue Jan 29 2002  </font></td></tr></table><p><table width=100%><tr><td><HR><font face=arial size=2 color=#FFFFFF>By the way... the only decent game WOTC ever produced was L5R.. the rest have started good but then sucked....<br>
